  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Abdominal surgery impairs ventilation. Postoperative pain accounts for this impairment.
      Regional analgesia is known to reduce pain, thus to limit ventilatory impairment. The
      investigators hypothesized bilateral continuous transverse abdominal plan block would reduce
      ventilatory impairment following abdominal surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
